  {
    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "We can't just move the tests in `provisionerd_test.go` over wholesale, because they work by setting up the whole omelette.  They'd have to be refactored.  Then also, we'd want some tests that actually test the provisionerd logic (connecting, acquiring jobs, etc.).\r\n\r\nIt's a good idea, and I'm happy to do it, but I'm not convinced it's the best use of my (or anyone's, really) time right now.  WDYT @kylecarbs ?\r\n",
    "created_at": "2022-07-01T16:49:45Z",
    "html_url": "https://github.com/coder/coder/pull/2732#issuecomment-1172536726",
